	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=25737&mid=109421840386185>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=25737&mid=109421840386185>How LDoN points work, with your teacher Joe Ogre!</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=25737&mid=109421840386185#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Sep 3rd 9:33 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=402869><span id= >DeaknightTheNecro</span></a><br><span id=notbold>7 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>It seems that after all this time some people still dont understand LDoN points, so here is the answer.<br><br>Once you have earned enough points to buy a LDoN item at a camp you can buy as many LDoN items from that camp as you want with points earned from any camp, solong as your points earned at that camp meet or exceed the point cost of the item.<br><br>The most points anything costs on the date of this post is 1492. Therefore once you have earned 1492 points at a LDoN camp you can buy ANY item at that camp provided you have enough points from any camp.<br><br>For those of you who still dont get it (or just the mentally handicapped):<br>Example<br>Joe Ogre is a lvl 25 Warrior, Joe has done 20 LDoNs! Joe Ogre says &quot;WHEEEE. JOE SMASH!&quot;<br>Joe has 20 LDoN points<br>10 from BB LDoNs<br>5 from EF LDoNs<br>5 from NRo LDoNs<br><br>Joe wants to buy <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=24252 target=akztarg>Sand-Encrusted Hammer</a><br>but Joe only has 5 whole LDoN points from EF /em cries!<br><br>In his sad and dejected state he wanders over to the BB LDoN camp (He still has to get that adventurers stone dontcha know! But thats like a QUEST!)<br><br>He finds to his shock that he CAN buy BOTH <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=23752 target=akztarg><br>Bloodstained Hammer</a><br>and<br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=23753 target=akztarg>Decaying Visor</a><br>After all he earned the minimum 10 points from BB, and had the required 20 total points needed to buy the items.<br>Joe Ogre is now L33T UBER!!! or is that UBER 133t!<br><br>Joe Ogre says &quot;Duh, 'Dat sure wuz HARD math, but me feels better now dat me dun it! JOE SMASH!&quot;<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Sep&nbsp;&nbsp;3 09:35:03 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>I am Necro</td></tr>
