	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=25737&mid=109217260365664>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=25737&mid=109217260365664>RE: augment</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=25737&mid=109217260365664#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Aug 10th 5:16 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122519><span id= >Astroshak</span></a><br><span id=notbold>40 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.11]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Yes and no.<br><br>When you complete an adventure, you get points.&nbsp;&nbsp;The number of points you get is added to two totals.  One of these totals is the number of Available Points that you have to spend.  The other is the total points you've earned in that theme.  <br><br>Unless the item you want to buy is not theme specific (most items are, the 1-6 point augs are perfect examples of items that are not), two conditions must be met for you to buy an item:<br>A) Your Points Available must equal or exceed the point value of the item you want to buy.  <br>B) Your total points earned in the theme must be greater than or equal to the point value of the item you want to buy.<br>Note that when you buy an item, the points for it are deducted only from the Points Available total, never from the points earned in the theme total.  So if you earn the 1150 points required to buy this aug solely in EC's dungeons, and then earn another 1150 points from the other 4 themed, you can buy TWO 1150 point items from EC vendors, though you cannot buy anything costing more than 1150 points from an EC vendor until you do more adventures here.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
